@flexiarg war-room/wr-8-typed-files-are-sources-of-truth
@title WR-8: Typed Files Are Sources Of Truth, Prose Is Regenerated
@sigils [⚖/令]
@audience futon stack operators, agents, mission authors
@tone foundational
@style pattern

! conclusion: Make the typed argument files the canonical self-model and generate prose from them, so drift becomes detectable instead of perennial.

  + context: War Room decision WR-8 (2026-04-24). Operator: Joe.

  + IF:
    The holistic argument was historically maintained as prose, the argument sketch and the aif2 argument.

  + HOWEVER:
    Prose drifted from intent because there was no machine-readable intent it had to track: every re-render was an editorial interpretation.

  + THEN:
    The sixteen leaf-level and one stack-level typed argument files at the futon5a stories are the canonical self-model. Prose deliverables are generated by renderers and re-rendered when the drift detector reports a source change. Editing prose in place is a defect.

  + BECAUSE:
    The typed argument format carries structure, claims, supports, attacks, falsifiability, and conflicts, that prose flattens. If the typed structure is canonical, drift between argument and document becomes detectable instead of perennial.

    + evidence: Sixteen leaf files plus the stack file encode all argumentative structure that prose previously asserted informally. A live endpoint projects this structure with a mission overlay and feeds the Web War Machine demo. Bulletin 8 documents the encoding effort and the prose-as-derived contract.
